Sentencas: The Ln(1.7)Sr(0.3)CuO(4) (Ln = Nd, La), i.e., NSCu and LSCu materials with perovskite-related structure were synthesized and evaluated as new cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Characterization and optimization of Ln1.7Sr0.3CuO4 (Ln = La, Nd)-based cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and electrochemical performance of Ln(1.7)Sr(0.3)CuO(4)
Titulo: Characterization and optimization of Ln1.7Sr0.3CuO4 (Ln = La, Nd)-based cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: cathodes have been investigated by X-ray diffraction, dilatometry, DC four-probe method, AC impedance and cyclic voltammetry (CV) techniques.
Titulo: Characterization and optimization of Ln1.7Sr0.3CuO4 (Ln = La, Nd)-based cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The conductivity of NSCu and LSCu reached 106 S cm(-1) and 125 S cm(-1) at 800 degrees C. NSCu cathode exhibited much lower area specific resistances (ASR) than LSCu, e.g., the ASR values for NSCu cathode on Sm-doped ceria (SDC) electrolyte in air were 0.07 Omega cm(2), 0.09 Omega cm(2) and 0.24 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C, 750 degrees C and 700 degrees C, while the corresponding values for LSCu were 0.11 Omega cm(2), 0.21 Omega cm(2) and 0.44 Omega cm(2), respectively.
Titulo: Characterization and optimization of Ln1.7Sr0.3CuO4 (Ln = La, Nd)-based cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: To further optimize the electrochemical performance of the cathodes, a certain amount of Sm-doped ceria (SDC) electrolyte was introduced.
Titulo: Characterization and optimization of Ln1.7Sr0.3CuO4 (Ln = La, Nd)-based cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of NSCu-SDC30 and LSCu-SDC30 was 0.12 Omega cm(2) and 0.18 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C in air, nearly half of pure NSCu and LSCu, respectively.
Titulo: Characterization and optimization of Ln1.7Sr0.3CuO4 (Ln = La, Nd)-based cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
